1
00:01:15,275 --> 00:01:17,341
Smile, damn you.

2
00:01:17,343 --> 00:01:19,409
Smile!

3
00:01:32,189 --> 00:01:34,622
Shut the door.

4
00:01:34,624 --> 00:01:37,424
What do you want?

5
00:01:37,426 --> 00:01:40,593
I have a job for you.

6
00:01:40,595 --> 00:01:42,795
What kind of job?

7
00:01:42,797 --> 00:01:44,830
<i>It's heavy work.</i>

8
00:01:44,832 --> 00:01:47,866
Digging.
We'll need another man.

9
00:01:47,868 --> 00:01:52,836
- When do you want it done?
- Some night soon.

10
00:01:52,838 --> 00:01:54,804
Where?
<i>The graveyard.</i>

11
00:01:54,806 --> 00:01:58,473
Unless you're afraid.

12
00:02:00,643 --> 00:02:05,111
The job pays two dollars.
Take it or leave it.

13
00:02:05,113 --> 00:02:07,346
I'll take it.

14
00:02:09,149 --> 00:02:12,850
But the job pays three dollars.

15
00:02:12,852 --> 00:02:15,285
Unless you think
I deserve more.

16
00:02:15,287 --> 00:02:18,888
No. Three dollars
seems fair enough. Yep.

17
00:02:36,704 --> 00:02:37,204
¶¶

18
00:02:53,686 --> 00:02:56,420
And where do you think
you're going?

19
00:02:56,422 --> 00:02:59,523
Go back to sleep, sid. I'm
just runnin' away from home.

20
00:02:59,525 --> 00:03:04,160
Again?
This time for sure.

21
00:03:05,863 --> 00:03:09,631
Me and Joe Harper and Ben Rogers
is goin' to new Orleans...

22
00:03:09,633 --> 00:03:12,767
To be steamboat men. Not
if I tell aunt Polly.

23
00:03:14,804 --> 00:03:17,871
I knew you were gonna be your
annoying little self, sid.

24
00:03:17,873 --> 00:03:20,607
So I rigged up
a little surprise for ya.

25
00:03:20,609 --> 00:03:23,209
There.
And so you don't get lonely...

26
00:03:26,314 --> 00:03:31,649
now, that right there is the most
poisonous spider in the whole world.

27
00:03:31,651 --> 00:03:35,786
If you knock that glass over,
she's gonna be pretty angry.

28
00:03:35,788 --> 00:03:38,822
'Course, it could just be
a little harmless fruit spider.

29
00:03:38,824 --> 00:03:42,292
But, only one way
to find out, right?

30
00:04:23,301 --> 00:04:26,302
<i>Howdy, boys!</i>

31
00:04:26,304 --> 00:04:28,304
Hey, muff.
Yeah, hey, muff.

32
00:04:28,306 --> 00:04:30,506
Where are you headed
this hour of the night?

33
00:04:30,508 --> 00:04:32,941
We're runnin' away from home.
<i>Uh-huh.</i>

34
00:04:32,943 --> 00:04:37,578
I used to do that all the time,
until home ran away from me.

35
00:04:37,580 --> 00:04:39,947
<i>Where'd they go?</i>

36
00:04:39,949 --> 00:04:42,582
As far away as they could.

37
00:04:43,551 --> 00:04:45,551
Come on.

38
00:04:45,553 --> 00:04:48,954
Don't let me stop you.

39
00:04:48,956 --> 00:04:51,957
Hey, when ya comin' back?

40
00:04:51,959 --> 00:04:54,025
Never!
Yep, never!

41
00:04:54,027 --> 00:04:56,327
Never, huh?

42
00:04:59,632 --> 00:05:02,566
See ya tomorrow.

43
00:05:25,490 --> 00:05:29,758
Bye, bye, Hannibal. Good-bye!
We're gonna be steamboat men.

44
00:05:31,328 --> 00:05:34,929
Left and bring her into the wind, Mr.
Harper. Aye, sir.

45
00:05:34,931 --> 00:05:37,331
Steady, now, steady.

46
00:05:37,333 --> 00:05:40,634
Steady it is, sir.

47
00:05:40,636 --> 00:05:44,471
Next stop, new Orleans.
Nothing can stop us now.

48
00:05:49,977 --> 00:05:53,345
- Hard to port! Hard to port!
- What's port?

49
00:05:53,347 --> 00:05:56,047
To the left!
No, it's right!

50
00:05:56,049 --> 00:05:58,482
<i>To the right then. Just pull it, Joe.
Pull it!</i>

51
00:05:58,484 --> 00:06:00,917
<i>Come on, Joe!
Pull!</i>

52
00:06:24,407 --> 00:06:26,974
All right. Tom, tom.
Tom! Tom!

53
00:06:26,976 --> 00:06:30,110
<i>Tom!</i>

54
00:06:50,430 --> 00:06:52,897
<i>Tom! Tom!</i>

55
00:07:00,872 --> 00:07:04,840
You all right, tom? Yeah, yeah.
Of course I'm all right.

56
00:07:04,842 --> 00:07:07,976
If it hadn't been for...

57
00:07:07,978 --> 00:07:11,079
Whoever it was,
you'd have been a goner.

58
00:07:11,081 --> 00:07:14,749
Town? Town. Come on.

59
00:07:31,834 --> 00:07:34,433
Bye, tom.

60
00:07:54,552 --> 00:07:57,119
Mornin', everybody.
What's for breakfast?

61
00:07:57,121 --> 00:08:01,889
Well, you can start...
With this.

62
00:08:01,891 --> 00:08:04,691
<i>Eeow.</i>

63
00:08:04,693 --> 00:08:06,959
Couldn't I just have
some scrambled eggs?

64
00:08:06,961 --> 00:08:11,029
Tom, I have a notion
to skin you alive.

65
00:08:11,031 --> 00:08:14,098
Sneaking out 'til all hours!
Worrying a body to death!

66
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:16,700
Yeah. Shall I get
the switch?

67
00:08:16,702 --> 00:08:21,471
I swore to your mama, my own sister, on her
deathbed that I would raise you proper.

68
00:08:21,473 --> 00:08:23,806
And you're doin' a fine job. No.

69
00:08:23,808 --> 00:08:26,575
I know I am not doing
my duty by you.

70
00:08:26,577 --> 00:08:28,710
I'll get the switch.
No!

71
00:08:30,780 --> 00:08:35,816
I'll just be obliged
to make you work tomorrow.

72
00:08:35,818 --> 00:08:39,219
Tomorrow? Couldn't I
just take a whippin'?

73
00:08:39,221 --> 00:08:42,889
I have got to do something, and I
ain't got the heart to hit you.

74
00:08:42,891 --> 00:08:45,157
<i>Now sit.</i>

75
00:09:31,769 --> 00:09:36,104
<i>¶ toot, toot ¶</i>

76
00:09:36,106 --> 00:09:40,141
<i>¶ toot, toot ¶</i>

77
00:09:40,143 --> 00:09:43,911
<i>¶ toot, toot ¶</i>

78
00:09:43,913 --> 00:09:47,114
<i>¶ toot, toot ¶</i>

79
00:09:47,116 --> 00:09:49,950
¶¶ ¶ toot, toot ¶

80
00:09:49,952 --> 00:09:52,619
¶¶

81
00:09:52,621 --> 00:09:55,588
Are you feeling okay, tom?

82
00:09:55,590 --> 00:09:58,958
Hi, Billy. I was havin' so much
fun, didn't even hear you comin'.

83
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:02,027
Fun? Whitewashin'
this here fence.

84
00:10:07,133 --> 00:10:12,535
Nah. That ain't fun.
That's work.

85
00:10:12,537 --> 00:10:15,838
Billy, if this was work,
would I be doin' it?

86
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:19,741
Ain't every day a boy gets
to whitewash a fence.

87
00:10:19,743 --> 00:10:22,276
Say, tom?
Hmm?

88
00:10:22,278 --> 00:10:25,912
Let me whitewash a little?

89
00:10:27,982 --> 00:10:31,016
Aunt Polly's awful particular
about this fence.

90
00:10:31,018 --> 00:10:33,051
<i>Just a little.</i>

91
00:10:33,053 --> 00:10:35,653
I'd like to help you out, bill.
Honest injun.

92
00:10:35,655 --> 00:10:38,589
But if you were to tackle this here fence,
and anything was to happen to it...

93
00:10:38,591 --> 00:10:41,825
I'll be real careful.

94
00:10:42,694 --> 00:10:45,161
What'll you give me?

95
00:10:45,163 --> 00:10:47,062
Uhh...

96
00:11:25,268 --> 00:11:27,868
oop! Oooh!

97
00:11:28,670 --> 00:11:30,702
<i>Huck!</i>

98
00:11:34,274 --> 00:11:37,975
You're back! Where'd you go?
Where've you been?

99
00:11:37,977 --> 00:11:40,644
Well, I'm a traveler.

100
00:11:40,646 --> 00:11:42,912
I go lots of places.

101
00:11:42,914 --> 00:11:46,115
Go upriver, downriver.
No place particular.

102
00:11:46,117 --> 00:11:49,751
I'm bound to pass through here
sometime.

103
00:11:51,721 --> 00:11:55,155
You're the one who pulled
me out the other night.

104
00:11:56,925 --> 00:11:59,625
I felt like a swim.

105
00:11:59,627 --> 00:12:02,160
Come on.
I'll show you my place.

106
00:12:04,831 --> 00:12:07,965
So how long you been
livin' here, huck?

107
00:12:07,967 --> 00:12:10,300
About a month.

108
00:12:10,302 --> 00:12:13,703
A month, huh?
Uh-huh.

109
00:12:13,705 --> 00:12:15,771
Well?

110
00:12:18,375 --> 00:12:21,309
Whoa!

111
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:28,715
Last week, aunt Polly whupped me for swipin'
a pie that was coolin' on the windowsill.

112
00:12:28,717 --> 00:12:31,984
<i>But it wasn't me.
Figured it was sid.</i>

113
00:12:31,986 --> 00:12:35,787
- He wanted it, but I beat him to it.
- I oughta punch you in the nose.

114
00:12:38,358 --> 00:12:41,392
You're welcome to try.

115
00:12:41,394 --> 00:12:44,028
Maybe later.

116
00:12:46,098 --> 00:12:50,467
<i>So, when you're not stealin' food
and savin' folks from drownin',</i>

117
00:12:50,469 --> 00:12:55,138
<i>what do you do all day?
</i> Whatever I want.

118
00:12:58,810 --> 00:13:00,910
Sure are lucky.

119
00:13:00,912 --> 00:13:04,313
Yep.
I'm a free man.

120
00:13:07,184 --> 00:13:11,252
Go wherever I want when I wanna go there,
do whatever I want when I want to do it.

121
00:13:11,254 --> 00:13:13,354
It's as simple as that.

122
00:13:20,496 --> 00:13:22,529
It's good to see ya.

123
00:13:22,531 --> 00:13:24,564
What's that for?

124
00:13:24,566 --> 00:13:27,133
It's what friends do.

125
00:13:27,135 --> 00:13:29,268
We friends?

126
00:13:32,940 --> 00:13:36,441
It's up to you.

127
00:13:36,443 --> 00:13:38,943
If your aunt Polly
catches you and me,

128
00:13:38,945 --> 00:13:41,211
she'll whup you
from here to St. Louis.

129
00:13:41,213 --> 00:13:45,081
This has nothin' to do with her. We was
friends before. Don't you remember?

130
00:13:45,083 --> 00:13:47,950
Yeah, I guess we were.

131
00:13:47,952 --> 00:13:50,585
Now we're friends again.

132
00:13:50,587 --> 00:13:53,053
Yeah, I guess we are.

133
00:13:55,991 --> 00:13:57,957
<i>We won't do it again,
will we?</i>

134
00:13:57,959 --> 00:14:01,060
Will we? I can't hear you.
Uh-uh.

135
00:14:06,233 --> 00:14:09,267
Thomas Sawyer!

136
00:14:09,269 --> 00:14:12,069
<i>Sorry I'm late for school,
Mr. dobbins.</i>

137
00:14:12,071 --> 00:14:16,173
Well, what's your excuse
this time?

138
00:14:16,175 --> 00:14:18,375
I stopped to talk
with huckleberry finn.

139
00:14:20,612 --> 00:14:23,045
Thomas Sawyer!

140
00:14:23,047 --> 00:14:26,848
That is the most
astounding confession...

141
00:14:26,850 --> 00:14:29,350
I have ever had to listen to.

142
00:14:29,352 --> 00:14:32,419
Yes, sir.
<i>You are not unaware...</i>

143
00:14:32,421 --> 00:14:35,555
That it is forbidden
to converse with that...

144
00:14:35,557 --> 00:14:38,291
Idle wastrel?

145
00:14:38,293 --> 00:14:42,962
No, sir.
I-I mean, yes, sir.

146
00:14:42,964 --> 00:14:45,965
You know, of course, that I shall
have to punish you. <i>Oh, no.</i>

147
00:14:45,967 --> 00:14:51,002
No, Mr. dobbins, please. You
wouldn't make me sit with the girls.

148
00:14:53,506 --> 00:14:56,139
Once again, Thomas Sawyer,

149
00:14:56,141 --> 00:14:59,608
you have outsmarted yourself.

150
00:15:02,212 --> 00:15:04,345
Ahh, ahh, ahh, ahh, ahh.

151
00:15:04,347 --> 00:15:06,947
<i>Grade seven's green book.</i>

152
00:15:10,385 --> 00:15:14,620
<i>"A Missouri maiden's farewell
to Alabama."</i>

153
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:18,957
<i>"Alabama, good-bye.
I love thee well.</i>

154
00:15:18,959 --> 00:15:22,593
<i>"For, yes, for a while
do I leave thee now.</i>

155
00:15:22,595 --> 00:15:24,962
<i>"Sad? Yes.</i>

156
00:15:24,964 --> 00:15:27,898
<i>"Sad thoughts of thee
my heart doth swell...</i>

157
00:15:27,900 --> 00:15:31,534
<i>"And burning recollections
from my brow.</i>

158
00:15:31,536 --> 00:15:34,303
<i>"For I have wandered through...</i>

159
00:15:34,305 --> 00:15:37,606
<i>"Thy flowery woods.</i>

160
00:15:37,608 --> 00:15:41,610
<i>"Have roamed and read here
tallapoosa's stream.</i>

161
00:15:41,612 --> 00:15:44,613
<i>Have listened
to Tallahassee's... "</i>

162
00:15:44,615 --> 00:15:48,583
<i>who belongs to this peach?</i>

163
00:15:48,585 --> 00:15:53,487
<i>Becky Thatcher,
do you belong to this peach?</i>

164
00:15:53,489 --> 00:15:59,459
<i>You will not abandon unconsumed
food in my school. Do you hear?</i>

165
00:16:25,052 --> 00:16:27,152
Whoa!

166
00:16:35,228 --> 00:16:39,063
Whew!
Hello, huck.

167
00:16:39,065 --> 00:16:41,732
Hello, yourself,
and see how you like it.

168
00:16:43,368 --> 00:16:45,701
Whatcha doin' here?

169
00:16:45,703 --> 00:16:48,236
<i>Lookin' for jackasses.</i>

170
00:16:48,238 --> 00:16:50,304
Under a bridge?

171
00:16:50,306 --> 00:16:54,340
I found one, didn't I?

172
00:16:56,110 --> 00:16:59,111
You gonna let her
do that to you?

173
00:16:59,113 --> 00:17:01,613
It's 'cause she likes me.

174
00:17:01,615 --> 00:17:06,216
She pushes you off a bridge 'cause
she likes you? Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

175
00:17:07,752 --> 00:17:11,019
I think you're both crazy.

176
00:17:12,055 --> 00:17:14,989
Hey, huck, what you got
in the sack?

177
00:17:14,991 --> 00:17:17,591
A dead cat.

178
00:17:17,593 --> 00:17:20,760
Wagon run over him.
Guts come out both ends.

179
00:17:20,762 --> 00:17:24,997
What's a dead cat
good for?

180
00:17:24,999 --> 00:17:27,299
To cure warts with.

181
00:17:27,301 --> 00:17:30,602
I got one.
How's it work?

182
00:17:30,604 --> 00:17:34,305
You take your dead cat to the graveyard
on the day somebody wicked's been buried.

183
00:17:34,307 --> 00:17:37,474
When the devil comes, you heave
your dead cat at him and say,

184
00:17:37,476 --> 00:17:40,610
"devil follow corpse.
Cat follow devil.

185
00:17:40,612 --> 00:17:43,212
Warts follow cat.
I'm done with you."

186
00:17:43,214 --> 00:17:46,048
That'll fetch any wart.
<i>Sounds right.</i>

187
00:17:46,050 --> 00:17:49,484
- So when you gonna try?
- Tonight.

188
00:17:49,486 --> 00:17:52,420
Let me go with ya, huck.

189
00:17:53,689 --> 00:17:55,755
You might get scared.

190
00:17:55,757 --> 00:18:00,059
I ain't scared of nothin'.

191
00:18:18,378 --> 00:18:21,345
Dead seems kinda lively tonight,
don't they?

192
00:18:21,347 --> 00:18:24,214
Baah!

193
00:18:24,216 --> 00:18:26,583
<i>Be careful!</i>

194
00:18:32,490 --> 00:18:34,690
Hmm.

195
00:18:38,362 --> 00:18:42,197
<i>- Who are they?
- The two on the right ain't so bad.</i>

196
00:18:42,199 --> 00:18:46,067
<i>The skinny one's doc Robinson,
and the fat one's muff Potter.</i>

197
00:18:46,069 --> 00:18:51,238
<i>Muff wouldn't hurt a fly.
That third fellow there?</i>

198
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:54,507
That's injun Joe.
Injun Joe?

199
00:18:54,509 --> 00:18:57,643
You know him?

200
00:18:57,645 --> 00:19:00,212
Let's just say I met him once,

201
00:19:00,214 --> 00:19:02,714
and I ain't in a hurry
to meet him again.

202
00:19:05,752 --> 00:19:09,119
They're goin' for
one of them old graves.

203
00:19:18,128 --> 00:19:20,161
That's it. That's it.

204
00:19:20,163 --> 00:19:22,296
W-would it be all right...

205
00:19:22,298 --> 00:19:26,866
If we stopped for a...
A little libation?

206
00:19:26,868 --> 00:19:30,636
What?
I need me a drink.

207
00:19:30,638 --> 00:19:34,172
No! Haul it up!
And hurry.

208
00:19:39,878 --> 00:19:44,680
<i>Yep! C'mon, c'mon.
Pry it open. Tip it over.</i>

209
00:19:49,886 --> 00:19:51,886
Murrell!

210
00:19:51,888 --> 00:19:56,290
One-eyed murrell?
My God!

211
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:09,168
Put the coffin back.
Cover up your tracks.

212
00:20:11,505 --> 00:20:15,273
Hey, not so fast. Get
your hands off me.

213
00:20:15,275 --> 00:20:19,743
Gimme that box. Doc, Joe, let's
talk this over like gentle...

214
00:20:20,879 --> 00:20:24,146
what'd you do that for?
That's just not right.

215
00:20:24,148 --> 00:20:26,214
Is it, doc?
Come here.

216
00:20:26,216 --> 00:20:29,417
<i>Come on, now. I got ya.
</i> It's a treasure map.

217
00:20:29,419 --> 00:20:32,219
<i>Oh!</i>

218
00:20:32,221 --> 00:20:36,622
Murrell's treasure?
Murrell's lost treasure?

219
00:20:36,624 --> 00:20:39,324
By glory, we're rich!

220
00:20:39,326 --> 00:20:41,426
<i>It's mine!</i>

221
00:20:41,428 --> 00:20:42,794
Oooh!

222
00:20:53,772 --> 00:20:56,372
No.

223
00:21:10,486 --> 00:21:14,887
What are you doing
with that thing?

224
00:21:55,929 --> 00:21:58,963
We gotta tell the sheriff.
<i>I ain't tellin' nobody.</i>

225
00:21:58,965 --> 00:22:01,899
Unless you're dumber than I think you are,
you're gonna keep your mouth shut too.

226
00:22:01,901 --> 00:22:03,901
But we seen a murder.

227
00:22:03,903 --> 00:22:06,803
Yeah. And there's gonna be two more
murders if we squeak on injun Joe.

228
00:22:06,805 --> 00:22:10,839
Killin' us would mean less to
him than drowning a few cats.

229
00:22:13,777 --> 00:22:18,746
I guess you're right.
We can't tell nobody.

230
00:22:20,382 --> 00:22:22,648
You're damn right.

231
00:22:22,650 --> 00:22:25,884
Just to make sure
you don't change your mind,

232
00:22:25,886 --> 00:22:28,553
we're gonna swear an oath.

233
00:22:28,555 --> 00:22:32,356
We'll write it down
and sign it in blood.

234
00:22:32,358 --> 00:22:34,725
Our blood?

235
00:22:34,727 --> 00:22:39,396
Unless you wanna go back and
borrow some from doc Robinson.

236
00:22:43,468 --> 00:22:47,469
You do it. I ain't
much good at writin'.

237
00:22:48,872 --> 00:22:51,839
Damn!
I lost my marble!

238
00:22:51,841 --> 00:22:54,508
We've got bigger things
to worry about.

239
00:22:54,510 --> 00:22:57,611
Now, would you please
write this down?

240
00:22:57,613 --> 00:23:01,314
I'm sorry.

